  "summary": "<a href=\"https://boingboing.net/2026/03/26/church-of-englands-first-woman-leader-installed-as-archibishop-of-canterbury.html\" rel=\"nofollow\" title=\"Church of England&#039;s first woman leader installed as Archibishop of Canterbury\"><img alt=\"\" class=\"webfeedsFeaturedVisual wp-post-image\" height=\"720\" src=\"https://i0.wp.com/boingboing.net/wp-content/uploads/2026/03/Mullally_2C-in-her-official-portrait.jpg?fit=1080%2C720&amp;quality=60&amp;ssl=1\" style=\"display: block; margin: auto; margin-bottom: 5px;\" width=\"1080\" /></a><p>The Archibishop of Canterbury leads the Anglican Communion, with <a href=\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/List_of_the_largest_Protestant_denominations\">some 100m adherents worldwide</a>. For the first time since its founding <a href=\"https://www.nbcnews.com/world/europe/sarah-mullally-archbishop-canterbury-first-woman-lead-church-rcna265053\">the position is now held by a woman, Sarah Mullally</a>, elected earlier this year and installed Wednesday.</p>\n<blockquote class",
